Well-travelled South African journalist and former radio presenter Redi Tlhabi has joined the BBC News World. Tlhabi, who presented The Redi Tlhabi show on Radio 702 for more than 10 years, is also a producer and author. She previously worked for Kaya FM, the SABC, and eMedia Holdings at eNCA. In her new job Tlhabi will present global news, current affairs including conducting compelling interviews on BBC World Service radio. Tlhabi shared that her show will run from 6am-9am South African time.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.